I recently visited Poke Bowl for lunch and was pleasantly surprised. It was a nice, warm, sunny afternoon, so a co-worker and I decided to venture outside. I suggested Poke Bowl because it was close enough to the office, and was also relatively healthy. We both ordered via the Yelp app. We had to wait for our order when we got there (there was a huge line out the door), but it was still ready before the indicated pick up time.  Normally, I'm pretty hesitant to try these "poke" spots because most of my experiences haven't been very good. I've learned that I can't be that poke snob who says, "It doesn't compare to the freshly-caught shoyu ahi poke I've had from a shack on the North Shore of Oahu." Of course it's not going to. This is New York City. Instead, I've learned to just call it what it is: a fancy sushi bowl, and I'm okay with that. I enjoyed every bit of my bowl, the masterpiece that I had crafted myself. As my base, I had zucchini noodles. For the protein, I got both salmon and tuna. Toppings were cucumbers, onions, seaweed salad, kani, fried garlic, jalapenos (be careful with these), all dressed with Sriracha aioli.  It is a bit further than I would normally care to venture during lunch, but I'll definitely be back next time I'm in the mood for some "poke bowls".

The portion is surprisingly generous, which I love. There are tons of quality toppings to choose from, even the more hard to find one. I would come here more often
Good food and very friendly staff. Portions are very generous. Salmon was so much fresher than the most shushi bars in NYC. You can see a dude constantly filleting fish on the side.

Nice addition to the FiDi area as lunch options are scarce. From the beginning the menu can be a bit overwhelming, but they also have a few pre-designed entrees to choose from. The staff was very helpful and friendly through the ordering process, the crab salad as delicious, and I highly recommend the crab guacamole. If you need something quick at a reasonable price for the area, definitely give it a try!
Poke serves very fresh salmon and you get a lot of food for your money.  Sushi burritto is very filling and priced below 10 dollars.  This is a steal in lower Manhattan.
Delicious, healthy fast food. The staff were friendly & the food was fresh & tasty.

I just loved it, the place is nice, the food was delicious, the price reasonable (cheaper than others I've tried in the area), and the young lady that was behind the counter was really nice, too. Only problem: the door doesn't close by itself and people aren't nice enough to close it, so next time I think I'm going to take it away, it was freezing!
The best food around! I loved sushi style burrito. It may be overwhelming what to chose, but you can't go wrong with one of the pre-set dishes.
Amazing addition to fidi! Food taste fresh and the service was friendly. I highly recommend the crab guacamole.
This has become my daily dinner. A long-awaited welcome to eastside Fidi dining. Love the toppings. Can't wait for delivery + android pay + loyalty options + more proteins.
